{"block": {"name": "code", "text": "<p><b><span class=\"wysiwyg-color-green\">Code Challenge:</span> Setting the Rightmost Bit</b></p><p>You will need to fill in the body of <span class=\"wysiwyg-font-tt\">setRightBit()</span>. The input will be a byte (i.e., 8 bits) <span class=\"wysiwyg-font-tt\">input</span> and a single bit <span class=\"wysiwyg-font-tt\">bit</span>, and you will need to set the rightmost bit of <span class=\"wysiwyg-font-tt\">input</span> to <span class=\"wysiwyg-font-tt\">bit</span> and return the result.</p><p>For example, if <span class=\"wysiwyg-font-tt\">input</span> is 254 (i.e., 1111111<b>0</b>) and <span class=\"wysiwyg-font-tt\">bit</span> is 1, the result would be 255 (i.e., 1111111<b>1</b>).</p>", "video": null, "animation": null, "options": {"limits": {"c++11": {"memory": 256, "time": 5}, "python3": {"memory": 256, "time": 15}}, "execution_memory_limit": 256, "code_templates": {"c++11": "unsigned char setRightBit(unsigned char input, unsigned int bit) {\n    // YOUR CODE HERE\n}", "python3": "def setRightBit(input, bit):\n    # YOUR CODE HERE"}, "execution_time_limit": 5, "samples": [["254 1", "255"]]}, "subtitle_files": [], "source": {"execution_memory_limit": 256, "samples_count": 1, "templates_data": "::python3\n::header\n::code\ndef setRightBit(input, bit):\n    # YOUR CODE HERE\n::footer\nfrom sys import stdin\nbyte,bit = stdin.read().strip().split(' ')\nprint(setRightBit(int(byte),int(bit)))\n\n::c++11\n::header\n#include <iostream>\n#include <set>\n#include <string>\nusing namespace std;\n\nunsigned char setRightBit(unsigned char input, unsigned int bit);\n\nint main() {\n    unsigned int byte;\n    unsigned int bit;\n    cin >> byte;\n    cin >> bit;\n    cout << (int)setRightBit((unsigned char)byte, bit);\n    return 0;\n}\n\n::code\nunsigned char setRightBit(unsigned char input, unsigned int bit) {\n    // YOUR CODE HERE\n}", "manual_memory_limits": [], "manual_time_limits": [], "is_memory_limit_scaled": true, "code": "imp